"'''A Certain Point of View'''" is a short story written by [[Charlene Newcomb]] (with illustrations by [[Mike Vilardi]] and [[Daniel Horne]]) that was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 8|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 8]] by [[West End Games]] in [[November]] [[1995]]. It was later reprinted in the short-story anthology ''[[Tales from the Empire]]'', which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in November [[1997]], and was also made available online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] on [[April 28]], [[2006]]. It takes place immediately after the [[Destruction of Alderaan/Legends|Destruction of Alderaan]] in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]].

==Plot summary==
The [[Kuari Princess/Legends|''Kuari Princess'']] was a [[Luxury liner/Legends|luxury liner]] that was operated by [[Galaxy Tours/Legends|Galaxy Tours]]. This particular trip was the [[Relgim Run/Legends|Relgim Run]], from [[Endoraan]] through [[Marmoth]], [[Aris/Legends|Aris]] and [[Vykos]] to [[Mantooine/Legends|Mantooine]], passing through the [[Maelstrom]] between Aris and Vykos.

[[Celia Durasha]], the young [[Navigator/Legends|navigation]] [[Officer/Legends|officer]] aboard the ''Kuari Princess'', is shocked to discover that her fellow crewmember, [[Security officer/Legends|security officer]], [[Detien Kaileel]], is a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] [[Agent/Legends|agent]]. Making this revelation especially difficult for her is news that Rebels [[Death/Legends|killed]] her brother, an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]], on [[Ralltiir/Legends|Ralltiir]]. Furthermore, her former boyfriend, [[Adion Lang]], has been assigned by the [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|Imperial Security Bureau]] (ISB) to [[Prison/Legends|arrest]] Kaileel. Following her conscience, Celia attempts to free Kaileel from shipboard detention, but Lang catches her red-handed, and shoots Kaileel. Celia attacks Lang, stabbing him with a [[Vibroblade/Legends|blade]], and escapes abord a [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle]] into the sensor-shrouding [[Maelstrom Nebula/Legends|Maelstrom Nebula]] to start life anew.

==Development==
[[File:RotM.jpg|thumb|150px|The cover that inspired the story]]
[[Star Wars Adventure Journal|Adventure journal]] editor [[Peter M. Schweighofer]] asked [[Charlene Newcomb]] to develop a story around an existing piece of artwork, a painting by [[Daniel Horne]] that adorned the cover of the [[Roleplaying game|roleplaying game]] adventure [[Riders of the Maelstrom (adventure)|Riders of the Maelstrom]] ([[1989]]). It featured a [[Human/Legends|human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] playing a [[Hologram/Legends|holographic]] chesslike game with a large [[Alien/Legends|alien]]. [[Celia Durasha|Celia]] would return in the short story ''[[Crimson Bounty]]''.<ref name="TERC" />

